          <msContents>
            <summary>
              <p>Single folio on parchment in horizontal format; Qurʾanic text: Q 27:14-27; 16 lines per page; AL-11 and another fragment from the same collection <ref target="https://corpuscoranicum.de/de/verse-navigator/sura/6/verse/71/manuscripts/1785">AL-16</ref> and three other fragments, two from the Freer Gallery collection <ref target="https://corpuscoranicum.de/de/verse-navigator/sura/35/verse/18/manuscripts/1273">F1945.19</ref> and <ref target="https://corpuscoranicum.de/de/verse-navigator/sura/26/verse/225/manuscripts/1274">F1945.20</ref> and one from Qatar National Library <ref target="https://corpuscoranicum.de/handschriften/index/sure/46/vers/16?handschrift=1418">HC.MS.2017.0010</ref> originally belonged to the same codex. For a detailed description of the sister fragments see the entry by Marcus Fraser <ref target="https://corpuscoranicum.de/handschriften/index/sure/46/vers/16?handschrift=1418">HC.MS.2017.0010</ref>.</p>
              <p>Cf. also the website of the institution: https://www.loc.gov/item/2019714721/</p>
            </summary>
            <msItem xml:id="mysql_id_698587" n="1r">
              <title type="numeric" key="027:019:018-027:027:003">
